Date: Tue 1 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Vietnam News Agency, Mon 28 Feb 2005 [edited]
<http://vietnamnews.vnagency.com.vn/showarticle.php?num=01HEA280205>

Viet Nam: Another Human Case of Avian Influenza in Thai Binh Province
---------------------------------------------------------------------
A 36-year-old man from a northern province is battling for his life in a
Hanoi hospital after contracting the [H5N1] strain of avian influenza virus
that has been affecting Viet Nam since last year [2004]. The Director of the
Department of Preventive Medicine and AIDS Prevention Trinh Quan Huan said a
man from the Vu Van Commune in the Vu Thu District was treated at the
Infection Faculty at Thai Binh Province General Hospital before being tested
for the virus at the Bach Mai Hospital, Institute of Clinical Research for
Tropical Diseases in Hanoi last Friday [25 Feb 2005].
Doctors treating the man, who is in critical condition, have said
that he contracted bird flu after coming into contact with infected
poultry. He is the 5th person to contract the virus in Thai Binh
Province so far in 2005.
On Sat 26 Feb 2005, the Animal Health Department, under the Ministry
of Agriculture and Rural Development, reported that 14 out of 35
previously affected provinces and cities have not reported any new
outbreaks of the disease in the last 3 weeks. These localities
include Kien Giang, Ninh Thuan, Dong Nai, Tien Giang, HCM City in the
south, Quang Binh, Nghe An in the centre, Lam Dong in the Central
Highlands, Ninh Binh, Ha Nam, Thai Nguyen, Phu Tho, Thai Binh and
Hanoi in the north. However, on Fri 25 Feb 2005, 11 new infection
hotspots were detected at poultry farms in 9 communes of 8 districts
of the Cuu Long (Mekong) Delta provinces of Bac Lieu, Long An, Dong
Thap, Ben Tre and Tra Vinh.
As of last Saturday [26 Feb 2005] 6000 ducks and geese have been
culled in the communes as part of an eradication programme.
